President Barack Obama has sent a notice to Congress stating that the national emergency with respect to the situation in or in relation to the Democratic Republic of the Congo is to continue beyond October 27, 2011. The President believes that the situation in the Congo, characterized by widespread violence and atrocities, poses a significant threat to regional stability and the foreign policy of the United States. Therefore, he has determined that it is necessary to continue the national emergency and the measures blocking the property of certain individuals contributing to the conflict in the country.